Global Military Unmanned Underwater Vehicles (UUV) Market Insights
Military Unmanned Underwater Vehicles (UUV) Market size was valued at USD 4.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 8.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.8% from 2024 to 2030.

Military Unmanned Underwater Vehicles (UUV) Market Overview
The global Military Unmanned Underwater Vehicles (UUV) market is projected to experience significant growth over the forecast period. In 2023, the market value was estimated at approximately USD 2.8 billion, and it is anticipated to reach USD 5.9 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 11.3%. The increasing focus on naval security, maritime surveillance, and underwater defense operations has been a major driver of market expansion. Military UUVs are used for intelligence, surveillance, reconnaissance, mine detection, and anti-submarine warfare, driving high demand from military and defense sectors globally.

